msContents.summary: Fragment of an Abbasid Qur'ān probably written in the third or fourth century H. / ninth or tenth century C.E, containing verses 75-87, 90-105, and 107-110 from Sura al-Kahf (سورة الكهف); verses 1-2, 13-19, 22-69, and 73-98 fom Sura Maryam (سورة مريم); and verses 10-28, 35-135 from Sura Ṭā-hā (سورة طه).

msItem.title: Sura Maryam: ninety-eight verses (سورة مريم تسعون وثمان) [line 2]

handNote.p: The script seems to correspond to the Abbasid Style NS I as described by François Deroche.

origin.origDate: 10th or 11th century AD /4th or 5th century Hijri
